12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 23 O.S. 2021, Section 61.2, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 Section 61.2. A. In any civil action arising from a claimed
16 bodily injury, the amount of compensation which the trier of fact
17 may award a plaintiff for economic loss shall not be subject to any
18 limitation.
19 B. Except as provided in subsection C of this section, in any
20 civil action arising from a claimed bodily injury, the amount of
21 compensation which a trier of fact may award a plaintiff for
22 noneconomic loss shall not exceed Three Hundred Fifty Thousand
23 Dollars ($350,000.00) Five Hundred Thousand Dollars ($500,000.00),
